ities harmed by environmental degradation. If the fate of Silicon Valley is the fate of America—as so many of its boosters claim—then this book gives us an unvarnished look into the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEquality-California-Santa Clara Valley (Santa Clara County). 0aHousing-California-Santa Clara Valley (Santa Clara County)-Pictorial works. 0aSanta Clara Valley (Santa Clara County, Calif.)-Pictorial works. 7aPhotography / General.2bisacsh1 aMeehan, Mary Beth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Fred, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTurner, Fred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226786513423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226786513/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles